Yeh line thodi powerful hai 💪 — ek baar samajh aa gayi toh kaafi kaam aayegi.


---

🔹 Code:

df["Marks"] = df["Marks"].apply(lambda x: x + 2)


---

🔥 Step-by-step samajh:

🔹 1. df["Marks"]

👉 Marks column select kiya


---

🔹 2. .apply(...)

👉 Har value pe same operation apply karega


---

🔹 3. lambda x: x + 2

👉 Yeh ek anonymous function hai (chhota function bina naam ka)

Matlab:

har value ko x maan lo

usme +2 add karo



---

📦 Example:

Pehle:

Marks
90
85
70

Apply ke baad:

92
87
72


---

🔹 4. df["Marks"] = ...

👉 Updated values ko wapas Marks column me store kar diya


---

🎯 Simple samajh:

👉 “Marks column ke har number me 2 add kar do”


---

💡 One-line yaad rakh:

👉 apply(lambda x: ...) = har value pe operation lagana


---

🔥 Exam/Viva tip:

lambda = short function

apply() = element-wise operation



